<h3 class="subsection"> 4.22.5 Various Tools </h3>

<p>BugPlug can do a lot more. Here is a summary of some of the more useful
features:
</p>
<ul>
<li>
Colorize sectors (<samp>&lsquo;ctrl-d ctrl-shift-c&rsquo;</samp>): with this feature BugPlug
will give every sector a random color. That way when you walk around your
world it is easy to see where a new sector starts.

</li><li>
Dump engine (<samp>&lsquo;ctrl-d d&rsquo;</samp>): dump all materials, meshes, sectors,
factories, and lights that are loaded. This can be a useful tool to see
what the engine currently contains. Note that it produces a lot of output.

</li><li>
Dump camera (<samp>&lsquo;ctrl-d shift-c&rsquo;</samp>): dump the contents of the current
camera (orientation, position, and <small>FOV</small>).

</li><li>
Change <small>FOV</small> (<samp>&lsquo;ctrl-d f&rsquo;</samp>): change the Field Of Vision setting.

</li><li>
List plugins (<samp>&lsquo;ctrl-d ctrl-alt-l&rsquo;</samp>): list all currently loaded plugins.

</li><li>
Click mesh (<samp>&lsquo;ctrl-s right-mouse-button&rsquo;</samp>): this doesn't select a mesh
but instead it prints out the mesh that was hit and the distance between
the camera and that mesh.

</li></ul>



